<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">
                            <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss> files, lot 59 D 237, “Slates”</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Director of the Office of
                                United Nations Political and Security Affairs</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_POPPERDH1"><hi rend="italic">Popper</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d307fn1">Addressed to
                                the four representatives of the geographic bureaus—<persName corresp="#p_MONSMAGN1">Monsma</persName> (<gloss target="#t_ARA1">ARA</gloss>), <persName corresp="#p_ALLENWP1">Allen</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>),
                                    <persName corresp="#p_HOWARDHN1">Howard</persName> (<gloss target="#t_NEA1">NEA</gloss>) and <persName corresp="#p_BACONRE1">Bacon</persName> (<gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>)—who together with a representative from the Bureau
                                of <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> Affairs constituted the
                                Department of State’s (United Nations) Membership
                            Team.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-04-30">April 30, 1954</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <item>Subject:</item>
                            <item>Ninth <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> Presidency</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>It is <gloss target="#t_UNA1">UNA</gloss>’s position that we should
                            decide now to support <persName corresp="#p_KLEFFENSEN1">Van
                                Kleffens</persName> for the presidency of the ninth <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> and so advise the Netherlands Government.
                            Attached is a draft cable to the Secretary requesting his concurrence in
                            this position. Could we please have your clearance or comment on the
                            draft as soon as possible.<note n="2" xml:id="d307fn2">Presumably no
                                action was taken because of the arrival of Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">Lodge</persName>’ telegram 678, Apr. 30,
                                6 p.m., <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note></p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>